36:48.100 --> 36:51.331
- You can do that?
- I can make him think it's happening.

36:51.370 --> 36:54.135
See, that's why
you look so sad, honey.

36:54.170 --> 36:56.400
You're wasting your time
trying to be a ghost.

36:56.440 --> 36:57.635
It's boring!

36:57.680 --> 37:00.843
- I know.
- But a poltergeist...

37:00.880 --> 37:02.439
Delicious!

37:05.020 --> 37:07.409
- What are you saying?

37:08.660 --> 37:11.015
- Get 'em off!
Get 'em off me!

37:11.060 --> 37:13.028
Get out of the way! Move!

37:13.060 --> 37:14.619
Get it off me!

37:14.660 --> 37:15.752
(Laughing)

37:15.800 --> 37:17.655
- Danny can't even hear me!

37:17.700 --> 37:19.190
How do you do that?

37:19.230 --> 37:22.063
- Honestly, for the first
5 years, I couldn't do squat.

37:22.100 --> 37:24.865
But for the past 15, hello!

37:24.910 --> 37:27.538
I know, I should probably
just kill him, right?

37:27.570 --> 37:28.537
Buzz kill!

37:28.580 --> 37:30.878
- Fatal-attraction ghost. Wow!

37:32.280 --> 37:33.748
(Laughing)

37:33.780 --> 37:35.771
So, what about your door?

37:35.820 --> 37:37.413
- My what?

37:37.450 --> 37:40.010
- Your door.
You know, how you move on.

37:40.050 --> 37:41.586
- Move on to what?

37:42.690 --> 37:45.523
I'm sorry, babe,
I gotta go.

37:45.560 --> 37:49.554
Bill hasn't gotten his rocks off in 5
years. You know why? Vigilance!

37:49.600 --> 37:52.023
Well, come find me
sometime, yeah?

37:52.070 --> 37:53.299
We'll get your guy.

37:53.330 --> 37:54.331
(Kissing)

37:54.370 --> 37:55.667
(Giggles)

38:04.780 --> 38:06.407
(Breathing heavily)

38:11.490 --> 38:13.049
- Well, now!

38:13.090 --> 38:14.558
- Sorry, did I...

38:14.590 --> 38:17.355
- Relax. I've got a good
right hook if I need it.

38:17.390 --> 38:19.279
- OK. Just...

38:19.330 --> 38:20.582
Am I being too...

38:20.630 --> 38:23.224
- You're being too polite.
- Yeah, I just...

38:26.470 --> 38:28.290
I just wanna make sure.

38:28.340 --> 38:29.466
Yeah...

38:29.500 --> 38:31.559
- What happened to you?

38:32.410 --> 38:34.208
(Door buzzing)

38:34.240 --> 38:37.232
(Both breathing heavily)

38:38.910 --> 38:41.140
- Just...
- Yeah, OK.

38:44.320 --> 38:45.913
(Exhales)

38:46.950 --> 38:48.486
- Ah jeez!

38:48.520 --> 38:49.487
- Sorry, sorry.

38:49.520 --> 38:51.579
You were heavy petting,
so I hid here.

38:51.630 --> 38:53.359
- Who are you talking to?

38:54.230 --> 38:57.052
- Who the hell
is here this late?

39:04.340 --> 39:05.762
Yes?

39:05.810 --> 39:07.039
- Bridget?

39:07.070 --> 39:08.435
- Bridget.

39:09.310 --> 39:10.903
- Have we met?

39:10.940 --> 39:14.240
- No, sorry.
I'm Josh.

39:14.280 --> 39:17.409
- Oh, right,
the boyfriend.

39:17.450 --> 39:18.781
- What?

39:18.820 --> 39:22.609
- Um... I think
this belongs here.

39:32.030 --> 39:35.364
- Isn't this Danny's?
- It's not Danny's. It's mine.

39:35.400 --> 39:37.061
(Rattling)

39:38.510 --> 39:40.308
(Clears throat)

39:40.340 --> 39:42.934
- Just put it somewhere, OK?

39:42.980 --> 39:45.244
I'm pretty sure
it belongs here.

39:45.280 --> 39:47.248
- OK.

39:49.120 --> 39:51.077
- Bridg...

39:51.120 --> 39:53.145
- Good night.

40:03.060 --> 40:04.869
- Uh...

40:13.310 --> 40:17.508
- Where to?
- Uh... I gotta go.

40:17.540 --> 40:18.871
- What?

40:18.910 --> 40:23.541
- I gotta... I left Emily and it's
late. I should take her home.

40:23.580 --> 40:25.514
- You're kidding me, right?

40:28.990 --> 40:30.412
- I...

40:30.460 --> 40:32.952
I really... No. No. No.

40:32.990 --> 40:34.060
I gotta go.

40:34.090 --> 40:38.049
- So, let the dog catcher
take her home.

40:38.100 --> 40:39.795
Come on.

40:40.970 --> 40:43.894
Ugh, I'm not doing
this for Bishop.

40:43.940 --> 40:45.430
I told you,
to hell with them.

40:45.470 --> 40:46.904
Doesn't that mean
anything to you?

40:46.940 --> 40:48.430
- Yes. Yes, it does.

40:48.480 --> 40:49.800
It really does.

40:49.840 --> 40:51.376
But I...

40:53.350 --> 40:55.546
I can't get into it tonight.

40:56.920 --> 40:59.014
- Ugh... Ugh!

40:59.050 --> 41:01.246
Maybe they have a point!

41:01.290 --> 41:03.281
Marcus and the rest.

41:03.320 --> 41:05.357
At least they
stick together.

41:18.710 --> 41:20.269
- I'm sorry.

41:29.650 --> 41:31.709
- You know, you, um...

41:31.750 --> 41:34.583
You really
don't have to go.

41:34.620 --> 41:36.213
- It's late.

41:36.260 --> 41:39.082
I should.
(Sighs)

41:50.170 --> 41:51.467
(Door opening)

41:51.500 --> 41:54.777
Did you arrange this or something?
- I swear...

41:54.810 --> 41:56.232
- Oh my God!

41:56.280 --> 41:57.839
- Josh...

42:01.110 --> 42:02.748
- Em!

42:02.780 --> 42:03.747
Oh no!

42:03.780 --> 42:05.817
What happened?
What happened?

42:05.850 --> 42:09.889
- I'm sorry, Josh. I know
you guys wanted to be alone.

42:09.920 --> 42:12.958
- I'm sorry. I-- - No, we're
taking her to the hospital.

42:12.990 --> 42:14.287
- I don't need to. I...

42:14.330 --> 42:17.493
I don't want you guys to--
- Hey, hey.

42:17.530 --> 42:19.123
We're going, OK?

42:19.170 --> 42:20.319
We're going.

42:20.370 --> 42:22.566
Can you stand?
Can you walk?

42:22.600 --> 42:26.901
- Mm-hmm.
- All right, come on. Come on. (Coughing)

42:51.600 --> 42:53.694
(Inhaling)

42:58.300 --> 43:01.600
** The stars wait
for a lot of days... *

43:01.640 --> 43:03.005
- Where are they?

43:03.040 --> 43:05.099
- The hospital.

43:05.150 --> 43:06.743
Aidan!

43:06.780 --> 43:08.839
* I'm tired of
the constellations *

43:08.880 --> 43:10.871
* Fights for euthanasia *

43:10.920 --> 43:14.311
* Did we ever really
land on the moon? *

43:19.490 --> 43:22.926
* Maybe there's a weight
on the words "I miss you" *

43:22.960 --> 43:24.394
* Do they impress you? *

43:24.430 --> 43:26.762
* That's the way love moves *

43:29.000 --> 43:31.389
* I'm tired of
the constellations *

43:31.440 --> 43:33.534
* And stars being
every solution *

